          this call to block() function does not work - documented bug in Twig 3
          https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/issues/3321

          {% with { dummyvar: 'YAHOOOOO' } %}
            {{ block('exampleblock', '@atoms/text/text/blockquote.twig') }}
          {% endwith %}
        #}
        {% include '@atoms/text/text/blockquote.twig' with quote_inline %}

        <h3>This is an Article Section Heading (H3)</h3>

        <p>In the years since, the hospital has expanded its programs and services, working with communities across Burera and providing lifesaving care in a rural district that once had no hospital.</p>

        {% include '@organisms/collections/tiles/tiles.twig' with {
          images: images.embeds.double,
        } %}

        <h4>This is an Article Section Heading (H4)</h4>
        <p>As programs and services have expanded, so too has demand. In 2012, just a year after opening, the hospital served 561 new patients in its oncology ward. By 2019, that number had surged to 1,770, reflecting an increased demand and fueling the need for growth.</p>
